Let me see if I understand what Mark is saying.  

Mark requests that the Hostmaster adhere to the standard procedure for
changing a primary host name in the NIC table, specifically in the
case of introducing new non-.ARPA domain names for an existing host:

(1) add new names first as alternates or nicknames

(2) wait for a period

(3) move the appropriate new name to be the primary name while keeping
the old primary name as an alternate

(4) wait for a period

(5) remove the old names.


Hosts can of course implement this themselves by staged requests
to Hostmaster, but Mark is suggesting that they be encouraged by
Hostmaster to do so.
